# next

Below is a clean, production-ready Jira Epic ‚Üí Story ‚Üí Sub-task structure based on your whiteboard content.
This is exactly how it should look when creating work items in Jira.

‚∏ª

üìå JIRA EPIC

EPIC: Implement End-to-End Data Ingestion & Connectivity Pipeline (Kafka + Terraform + Observability)

‚∏ª

üìå JIRA STORIES & SUB-TASKS

‚∏ª

User Story 1: Requirement Gathering & Analysis

As a Platform/Integration Engineer
I want to gather requirements and understand the current system
So that I can design and implement the target Kafka-based solution.

Sub-Tasks
	1.	Identify SMEs and schedule requirement sessions
	2.	Capture functional and non-functional requirements (SLAs, throughput, consumers)
	3.	Document current-state architecture and data flow
	4.	Identify all existing consumers and output systems
	5.	Create requirements summary document and circulate for sign-off

‚∏ª

User Story 2: Target-State Architecture & Design

As a Solution Architect
I want to design the target state for the ingestion pipeline
So that the implementation aligns with business and technical goals.

Sub-Tasks
	1.	Define target architecture diagram
	2.	List implementation steps and dependencies
	3.	Identify updates needed in Terraform module(s)
	4.	Define Kafka topic structure (name, partitions, replication, retention)
	5.	Review design with SMEs and finalize

‚∏ª

User Story 3: Terraform Implementation

As a Platform Engineer
I want to implement the infrastructure changes using Terraform
So that the environment can be provisioned reliably and consistently.

Sub-Tasks
	1.	Update or create Terraform module for Kafka components
	2.	Add configurations for Kafka topics, ACLs, and retention policies
	3.	Implement required cloud resources (IAM, security groups, networking)
	4.	Validate Terraform plan & fix issues
	5.	Execute Terraform apply in dev ‚Üí stage ‚Üí prod environments

‚∏ª

User Story 4: Kafka Topic Setup & Configuration

As a Kafka Engineer
I want to set up the Kafka topic and configure required properties
So that producers and consumers can interact with it reliably.

Sub-Tasks
	1.	Create Kafka topic per design
	2.	Configure partitions, replication, and retention
	3.	Set ACLs and schema registry rules (if applicable)
	4.	Validate topic creation in non-prod
	5.	Promote topic to production

‚∏ª

User Story 5: Implement Filtering / Transformation Logic

As a Data Pipeline Engineer
I want to build filtering/transformation logic
So that only required data is passed to downstream systems.

Sub-Tasks
	1.	Identify filters/transformation rules
	2.	Implement filtering logic
	3.	Implement transformation/enrichment components
	4.	Perform functional testing of logic
	5.	Validate performance and latency

‚∏ª

User Story 6: Implement Connectivity to Downstream Outputs

As a Integration Engineer
I want to connect Kafka data streams to the required output systems
So that downstream consumers receive the required data.

Sub-Tasks
	1.	Identify output systems (targets)
	2.	Implement connectivity components (connectors / APIs / sinks)
	3.	Configure credentials and access policies
	4.	Test end-to-end data flow
	5.	Validate output delivery with consumer teams

‚∏ª

User Story 7: Implement Observability Integration

As a Observability Engineer
I want to integrate the ingestion pipeline with monitoring & logging
So that the system is measurable and supportable.

Sub-Tasks
	1.	Configure metrics for Kafka producers/consumers
	2.	Enable logs collection for pipeline components
	3.	Configure traces (if applicable)
	4.	Create dashboards in Grafana/Kibana
	5.	Set up alerts for SLIs/SLOs

‚∏ª

User Story 8: Testing, UAT & Deployment

As a Platform Engineer
I want to test and deploy the pipeline
So that it can be used in production with confidence.

Sub-Tasks
	1.	Perform unit testing
	2.	Execute integration/E2E testing
	3.	Execute UAT with SMEs
	4.	Deploy to production
	5.	Validate observability, dashboards, and alerts

‚∏ª

User Story 9: Documentation & Handover

As a Platform/SRE Engineer
I want to document and handover the solution
So that support teams can maintain the system.

Sub-Tasks
	1.	Update architecture documentation
	2.	Write runbooks/SOPs
	3.	Document Terraform modules and variable usage
	4.	Conduct KT sessions with SRE/Support
	5.	Final sign-off and close the epic

